A
25, 25 \text{, and }30
S = \dfrac{25+25+30}{2}=40
Area_A = \sqrt{40(40-25)(40-25)(40-30)}
=\sqrt{40(15)(15)(10)}
=\sqrt{90000}
=300
B
25, 25 \text{, and }40
S = \dfrac{25+25+40}{2}=45
Area_B = \sqrt{45(45-25)(45-25)(45-40)}
 =\sqrt{45(20)(20)(5)}
=\sqrt{90000}
=300
Area_A:Area_B = 1:1
